Name: Central Ave & Clifton Cres, Inglewood

Comment 1: Poor enforcement of clearways causes traffic congestion on Beaufort St in peak periods.
Comment 2: Eileen: Walcott Street and Beaufort Streets  as well as the intersection have high pedestrian traffic, including many parents pushing prams. There is alfresco dining on the streets causing pedestrians to walk close to the roads.  Speed limits are far too high. There are no cameras at the traffic lights and there should be to slow down the vehicle speeds. Constantly there are accidents, including the areas near corners of Field and Walcott Streets, a bad accident recently when a car hit a lamp post.

Name: 79 Guildford Rd, Mount Lawley
Description: In the afternoons there are too many vechiles turning left onto Guilford and there's only 1 left turning lane and 2 right turning lanes. On Mondays (lowest fuel price day) this becomes particularly problematic due to vechiles queuing at the Puma petrol station. Vechiles bank up on Whatley as far back as the traffic lights on East Parade. I suggest that the middle lane is also made a left turning lane to allow for more vechiles to get through each traffic light phase.
